@startuml
' Evaluate chain — ralphctl sprint evaluate (standalone, single round)
' Standalone factory: src/application/chains/evaluate/evaluate-flow.ts
' Step trace: load-sprint → load-task → check-already-evaluated → evaluate-task → persist-evaluation
'
' The standalone chain runs ONE round per invocation. The multi-round
' fix-and-re-evaluate loop lives inside `execute/per-task-flow.ts` as
' `EvaluateAndFixLoopUseCase`, NOT here.
title ralphctl — Evaluate chain (single round, standalone)

autonumber

actor User
participant CLI as "CLI / TUI"
participant SM as "SessionManager"
participant Chain as "Sequential('evaluate')"
participant UC as "Use cases\n(business)"
participant AI as "AI\n(autonomous evaluator)"
database sprint.json
database tasks.json

User -> CLI : ralphctl sprint evaluate <taskId>
CLI -> SM : start({ element=createEvaluateFlow, ctx })
SM -> Chain : execute(ctx)
activate Chain

Chain -> UC : LoadSprintUseCase
note right: trace: load-sprint
UC -> sprint.json : findById

Chain -> UC : taskRepo.findById(sprintId, taskId)
note right: trace: load-task
UC -> tasks.json : findById

Chain -> Chain : task.evaluated === false
note right: trace: check-already-evaluated\n(returns NotFoundError 'unevaluated-task'\nto short-circuit if already evaluated —\nthe only step that fails the chain on\na business condition rather than an error)

Chain -> UC : EvaluateTaskUseCase\n+ previousCritique?
note right: trace: evaluate-task
UC -> AI : spawnHeadless(task-evaluation.md\n+ task + sprint + previousCritique?)
activate AI
note right: model ladder for Claude:\nOpus→Sonnet, Sonnet→Haiku, Haiku→Haiku\nCopilot: same model
AI --> UC : raw output
deactivate AI
UC -> UC : SignalParser.parse → EvaluationSignal\n(dimensions: **Name**: PASS|FAIL — finding)
UC --> Chain : { outcome, fullCritique }

Chain -> UC : task.recordEvaluation({\n  status, output: critique.slice(0, 2000),\n  file: 'evaluations/<taskId>.md'\n}) + taskRepo.update
note right: trace: persist-evaluation\n(records preview on Task aggregate;\nstandalone chain does NOT write the\nfull-critique sidecar — that adapter\nlives in the per-task chain)

Chain --> SM : Result.ok({ ctx, trace })
deactivate Chain
SM --> CLI : completed
CLI --> User : EvaluationSignal\n(passed / failed / malformed)

note over Chain
  Use case never blocks: malformed /
  failed evaluations resolve as
  Result.ok so the surrounding chain
  (whether standalone or per-task)
  always proceeds.
end note

@enduml
